   <body>
      <context>You can approve a pending user account registration for non-Active Directory users.  After approving the pending account, you will need to access the user account and assign roles to the new user. </context>
      <ol>
         <li>
            <p>In the module menu, click <uicontrol>Administration</uicontrol>.</p>
            <p>The <uicontrol>ADMINISTRATION</uicontrol> page is displayed.</p>
         </li>
         <li>
            <p>In the navigation pane, expand <uicontrol>User Management</uicontrol>, and then click <uicontrol>Pending Registrations</uicontrol>.</p>
            <p>The <uicontrol>PENDING REGISTRATIONS LIST</uicontrol> page is displayed.</p>
         </li>
         <li>
            <p>Select the required user registration request to approve.</p>
         </li>
         <li>
            <p>Click <uicontrol>Approve</uicontrol>.</p>
            <p>A confirmation message is displayed.</p>
         </li>
         <li>
            <p>Click <uicontrol>OK</uicontrol>. </p>
            <p>The user is added to the application database. You can view the user account in the <uicontrol>USER ACCOUNTS</uicontrol> page. <note> The approved user accounts require the Administrator to define the user details, roles, and business units. </note>
               <ph product="Exclude_PG_Content">For information on accessing the <uicontrol>USER ACCOUNTS</uicontrol> page, refer to<xref href="../../../CoSP/Administration/User_Management/User_Accounts/UserAccs.xml">User Accounts</xref>.</ph>
            </p>
         </li>
      </ol>
